## /write-plan Based on @docs/features/todo-list.md , implement the backend api, use react router api ssr. no golang no protobuf

1. Added backend DB connection module at `app/apps/web/app/db/client.server.ts` using `DATABASE_URL` and `pg` pool.
2. Added backend todo service module at `app/apps/web/app/services/todo.server.ts` with schema bootstrap, list/get/create/update/delete/dependencies/complete operations, optimistic locking (`updated_at`), `SELECT ... FOR UPDATE` transaction flow, dependency validation, recurrence generation, and soft delete support.
3. Added React Router SSR API routes:
   - `app/apps/web/app/routes/api.v1.todos.ts`
   - `app/apps/web/app/routes/api.v1.todos.$id.ts`
   - `app/apps/web/app/routes/api.v1.todos.$id.dependencies.ts`
   - `app/apps/web/app/routes/api.v1.todos.$id.complete.ts`
4. Updated API route registration in `app/apps/web/app/routes.ts` to expose `/api/v1/todos`, `/api/v1/todos/:id`, `/api/v1/todos/:id/dependencies`, and `/api/v1/todos/:id/complete`.
5. Updated `app/apps/web/app/routes/home.tsx` to use backend APIs instead of in-memory TODO state:
   - list via `GET /api/v1/todos`
   - create via `POST /api/v1/todos`
   - edit via `PUT /api/v1/todos/:id` only
   - delete via `DELETE /api/v1/todos/:id`
6. Updated `docs/features/todo-list.md` backend section to use React Router SSR TypeScript API (removed Golang/protobuf notes), added missing dependency/complete endpoints, and split create/update payload docs to make `PUT` update semantics explicit.

7. Debugged TODO API `GET` 500 error and confirmed root cause was missing runtime `DATABASE_URL`; updated API route error mapping files to return explicit config error message (`Server config error: DATABASE_URL is required`) instead of generic internal server error.
8. Updated `docs/features/todo-list.md` documentation section to explicitly note `DATABASE_URL` is required for local backend API runtime.

