## @app/apps/web/app/services/todo.server.ts use drizzle orm instead

1. Updated `app/apps/web/app/db/client.server.ts` to expose `getDb()` using `drizzle-orm/node-postgres` on the shared `pg` pool.
2. Refactored `app/apps/web/app/services/todo.server.ts` to run all database operations through Drizzle (`db.execute`, `db.transaction`) instead of direct `pool.query` / `client.query` calls, including list/count queries and transactional writes.

---

## why using client execute syntax? use orm related syntax instead

1. Added Drizzle table definitions in `app/apps/web/app/db/schema.ts` (`todo_items`, `todo_dependencies`) and wired `getDb()` to use `{ schema }` in `app/apps/web/app/db/client.server.ts`.
2. Refactored `app/apps/web/app/services/todo.server.ts` to use Drizzle query builders (`select`, `insert`, `update`, `delete`, `where`, `inArray`, `exists`, `count`, `for('update')`, etc.) instead of `db.execute(sql\`...\`)` for CRUD and listing; kept `db.execute(sql.raw(...))` only for one-off DDL in `ensureTodoSchema()`.
3. Normalized list/detail API rows to use `dependency_ids` (with `recurrence` built from stored type/config) so responses match the shared `todoSchema` / home UI.
4. `app/apps/web/app/db/client.server.ts`: accept `DATABASE_URL` or `VITE_DATABASE_URL` for the connection string (still throws `DATABASE_URL is required` when neither is set, for existing API error handling).
